<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-02T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-02T08:00:00-05:00" n="601" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.014/203: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-02T16:00:00+03:00">November
                                    2, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 2—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>850. The Supreme Soviet at its evening session yesterday acceded to the
                            petition of the National Assembly of Western Ukraine to incorporate that
                            territory into the Soviet Union as a part of the Ukrainian Soviet
                            Socialist Republic. According to the agenda, Western White Russia will
                            be incorporated this evening.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SLA1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>